    "Body": " Network Administrator Polar Field Services - 4.7 Mountain View, CA Quick Apply Job Details Full-time | TemporaryEstimated: $68,000 - $95,000 a year Benefits Employee Stock Ownership Plan Qualifications Network Monitoring Computer Networking Google Cloud Platform Communication Skills CPR Certification Bachelor's Degree Master's Degree Full Job Description Location: Mountain View, CA Reports to: PFS IT&C Manager Hours: 40+ hours per week, with evenings/nights and/or weekends depending on operations schedule. Multi-day overnight domestic and international travel may be required. Additional Information: This is a 6-month benefit-eligible temporary position with the potential to extend to regular full-time employment. Company Backgrounds: Polar Field Services, Inc. (PFS) is a woman-owned small business with an Employee Stock Ownership Program (ESOP). Formed in 1999, PFS has extensive experience planning and executing scientific, technical, construction, and operational support internationally and across the U.S. Our name reflects our dedication to field support at the extremes of the earth and anywhere in between: whether working in a snow storm or sand storm, PFS is built to support bespoke technical programs across the planet. X is an Alphabet company exploring innovative solutions to complex global problems. PFS is supporting a Free Space Optical Communications (FSOC) project in X involved in designing, testing, and deploying a high-speed wireless backhaul technology. Position Overview: The PFS X Network Administrator will work as part of an operations team developing, deploying, and testing network solutions for a high-speed wireless backhaul data network. This work will include monitoring, troubleshooting, and scaling operations of a Network Operations Center while working alongside engineers, technicians, customers, and 3rd party network partners. The Network Administrator will perform technical analysis of system issues and outages as they occur across a multitude of wireless backhaul data networks. The position will research and troubleshoot the issue to resolution, including escalating the issue to an R&D engineer when necessary. Travel may be required to international sites. The Network Administrator is responsible for researching, developing, and documenting mitigation strategies while effectively communicating in real-time with customers, including maintaining assurance that the immediate problem will be resolved. The position must maintain current and thorough knowledge of the technology and its significance to network operations and must be able to prioritize issues in a complex environment with critical uptime requirements. The Network Administrator requires discretion and judgement while cooperatively communicating with multiple stakeholders. The ideal candidate will be an active problem-solver comfortable working in a dynamic, rapidly changing environment. Primary Duties: Regular Tasking: Devise novel network connectivity solutions to enable remote management and monitoring of wireless backhaul network equipment that is embedded in large scale networks, within the constraints of customer\u2019s network security policies. Apply relevant tools to troubleshoot and interpret IP and basic RF signals. Assist in monitoring and implementing IP routing, troubleshooting, and other maintenance coordination activities as necessary Develop success criteria and automation for test processes for key network performance indicators and seamless integration into customers networks. Coordinate field testing, monitoring, and analysis of customer network systems. Perform system administration tasks such as network/system troubleshooting, remote restart and bring-up of wireless backhaul equipment, and execution of various scripts. Develop and document troubleshooting procedures, and train lower-level NOC team members in the execution of new procedures, including scenarios that involve network equipment from 3rd parties. Work with the NOC management team on the customer\u2019s side to improve operational efficiency as the NOC scales operations to monitor increasing numbers of wireless backhaul networks worldwide. Triage incidents escalated by lower-level NOC technicians. Spin up and configure Linux-based virtual machines in Google Cloud Platform. Write shell scripts and/or Python scripts to automate repetitive tasks. Support multiple technical teams in 24x7 operational environments with high uptime requirements General responsibilities: Ensure compliance with state, federal, and company environmental, health, and safety regulations and practices. Communicate closely with PFS and X management. Maintain prompt, consistent, and positive customer relationships. Clearly document all procedures within X-specific systems, including checklist documentation and troubleshooting. Provide continuous effort to improve operations, streamline processes, and work cooperatively and jointly to provide quality customer service. Must carry smart phone at all times when working and respond promptly. Other duties as requested and required. Qualifications: Minimum Academic Requirements: Bachelor\u2019s degree from an accredited college or university in engineering, mathematics, computer science, or physics. Required Knowledge, Skills and Aptitudes: General 5+ years of IT Network Administration and Telecommunication work experience Experience providing remote support using virtual network monitoring tools including Zabbix and Grafana Ability to recognize system performance anomalies from time-based data plots Extensive experience with Linux command line interface, shell scripts, Python scripts, crontab, and network configuration Fluency in networking fundamentals and communication protocols including TCP/IP, NAT, VPN, SNMP, and gRPC Experience managing projects in Google Cloud Platform and familiarity with interconnecting public cloud and private networks Ability to think creatively to resolve problems in ambiguous situations Previous NOC experience Strong communication and problem-solving skills with the ability to communicate clearly and calmly with customers and technical personnel in high-stress situations Project management and scheduling expertise Excellent written and verbal communication skills Discretion with sensitive customer information Experience with Google Suite and Microsoft Office Additional Requirements: Regular and predictable onsite attendance as well as availability to work extended hours, including afterhours/weekends and on-call. Ability to travel locally and internationally when necessary (up to 10% of the time). Authorization to work in the U.S. is a precondition of employment. Polar Field Services will not sponsor U.S. work visas. Possession of a current and valid US passport Preferred Skill Sets: Master\u2019s degree from an accredited college or university in engineering, mathematics, statistics, computer science, or physics Cisco/Juniper networking certifications or equivalent cloud/application certifications Experience establishing VPN tunnels between dissimilar network platforms Experience configuring Zabbix to efficiently support a large number of hosts Ability to manage mySQL and SQL databases Experience creating Grafana dashboards to display time-based data plots Fundamental understanding of IPv6 networking Fluency using Google Drive, Google Docs, Google Sheets, and Google Slides Current CPR, WFA, or WFR certification HSE: Adheres to Health, Safety and Environment policies in planning and execution of all activities. License Requirements: Current and valid driver\u2019s license with insurable Department of Motor vehicle record (parking violations, minor driving offenses excluded). Working Conditions: Normal office conditions, largely computer-based with some hands-on technical testing. Use of hand tools and power tools. This position may require occasional travel which includes long international plane rides, navigating and traversing unfamiliar locations, airports, cities, and environments during various times of day, various weather, and other unpredictable conditions. "
